Docs.summary: is an immutable value type that represents a floating type that has the same size as the native integer size. It is meant to be used as an exchange type at the managed/unmanaged boundary to accurately represent in managed code unmanaged APIs that use a type alias for C or C++'s float on 32-bit platforms or double on 64-bit platforms, such as the CGFloat type in libraries provided by Apple.

remarks.format:
